frameDefinitions: Partner_1 interacts with Partner_2 (also collectively expressible as Partners) to change their social relationship.
This frame describes a Theme losing its autonomy and perhaps sustaining material damage as the result of a successful invasion on the behalf of a Conqueror.
The words in this frame have to do with people and the personal Relationships they are or can be a part of.
A Surrenderer is compelled to transfer a Theme to a Recipient.
An Agent leaves behind a Theme effectively rendering it no longer within their control or of the normal security as one's property.
frameExamples: I <t>befriended</t> the little pony by giving him a piece of apple.
The Spaniards <t>conquered</t> the Incas with both the Cross and the arquebus
And of course that drippy <t><fex name='Partner_1'>boyfriend</fex></t> of hers backed her up.
Shortly after the boy <t>surrendered</t> the gun, the three remaining warriors made a rush for liberty.
Carolyn <t>abandoned</t> her car and jumped on a red double decker bus.
listRoleDefinitions: The individual who comes to form a relationship with Partner_2.
The individual whose relationship with <fen>Partner_1</fen> changes.
The individuals whose relationship is changing.
The time when the relationship changes.
Where the relationship is formed.
The <fen>Conqueror</fen> is the entity that overtakes the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the land, government, and its people that is seized by the <fen>Conqueror</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Conqueror</fen> seizes the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Conqueror</fen> takes over the <fen>Theme</fen>.
That partner in the <fen>Relationship</fen> who is realized as the subject of verbs in active form sentences, or of adjectives in predicative uses.
That partner in the <fen>Relationship</fen> who is not expressed as the external argument.
The joint construal of both <fen>Partners</fen> in the <fen>Relationship</fen>.
The person compelled to transfer the <fen>Theme</fen> to the <fen>Recipient</fen>.
The entity that ends up in possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The object that changes possession.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the <fen>Surrenderer</fen> gives the <fen>Theme</fen> to the <fen>Recipient</fen>.
The <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Surrenderer</fen> gives the <fen>Theme</fen> to the <fen>Recipient</fen>.
The <fex name='Agent'>Agent</fex> is the person who acts to leave behind the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fex name='Theme'>Theme</fex> is the entity that is relinguished to no one from the <fex name='Agent'>Agent</fex>'s possession.
When the <fen>Agent</fen> gives up the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> gives up the <fen>Theme</fen>.
